{"_id":"00a4gnS56r5shCLm","name":"Put your heart into it","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Empower trapped spells","description":"Temporarily decrease your Heart by 1 when you create a trapped spell (scroll, potion, etc.). You gain the Heart point back when the spell is released. When it is released, if the spell has been stored for more than one day, increase all the spell's numeric effects by \n * 1 (minor)\n * 2 (major)\n * 3 (grand)","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.00a4gnS56r5shCLm"}}}
{"_id":"2tDhM7teLQgIjUpN","name":"Atrocity","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Debuff enemies when you kill","description":"Your violence unnerves even veterans.\nWhen you kill an enemy in battle, all remaining opponents in the area\n * take 1 Mood damage (minor); \n * take 1 Mood damage and take a Heart penalty die on their next attack (major); \n * take 1 Mood damage, take a Heart penalty die on all rolls next round, and must make a Heart check against the Doom or rebalance (grand).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"3CrvjpKFAwQOIXD1","name":"Talisman","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Wild surges don't damage you","description":"A talisman is a luck charm against chaos, especially the chaos of magic. If you have the implement class ability and have selected the talisman, you are never damaged by a wild magic surge that you create. In addition, you can force any surge that targets you to re-roll its attack roll\n * once (minor)\n * twice (major). \nThe grand version of this talent works as described above, twice per scene, but is effective against crisis surges as well.","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3CrvjpKFAwQOIXD1"}}}
{"_id":"72mlZxkRRiExDuCh","name":"Rush","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Gain mood when you cast spells","description":"Increase your Mood by 1 whenever your Magic roll (or a magic attack roll) exceeds the Doom.\nYou can benefit from this ability\n * once per scene (minor)\n * twice per scene (major)\n * three times per scene (grand)","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.72mlZxkRRiExDuCh"}}}
{"_id":"9uA9BQGtUMOBgAr8","name":"Rip and break","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Damage stats with mastery attacks","description":"When you hit with a mastery maneuver, you can convert one point of the damage to characteristic damage (Strength, Quickness, or Reason). \nWith the major talent, you can convert up to two points to any two characteristics (out of Strength, Quickness, or Reason, no more than one point per characteristic).\nAs a grand talent, you can convert up to three points of damage to one point to all three characteristics. \n\nYou cannot use rip and break at the same time that you use another mastery maneuver talent (such as scimitar dervish, hammer knockback, etc.).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"AHG7iqkmoIpiFeW6","name":"Smith","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Cheaper and faster crafting","description":"When crafting a weapon, armor piece, engineering item, siege item, building or fortification, the cost of creating the item is only 40%, rather than 50%, of the item's gold value. Also,\n * reduce by one day the amount of time you must wait before attempting to add another quality point to the item (minor);\n * reduce that time by two days and ignore any critical failure rolls (major);\n * as the major talent, plus increase the final value of the item by two quality levels (grand).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"AqdJ5A7U0P9HRZp1","name":"Harrowing","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"You are a torturer","description":"Often useful as a threat during interrogations, you can create such a nightmarish durance vile for a captive that he is forced to take a scar (see p. 30) if he does not acquiesce to your demands.\nThe art of scarring the psyche as well as the body is difficult. You can give any particular captive such torture no more than\n * once (minor)\n * three times (major).\n * Or, it must be said, an unlimited number of times (grand), which leaves the captive a husk of a being, unable to recall any of its own history, only remembering the pain and fear you have left in its place.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"BbM6EfCT8qEU92of","name":"Intimidate","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Intimidate with Strength","description":"You can roll your Strength instead of Charisma as a social attack die whenever you attempt to intimidate your opponent. You can do this \n * once per scene (minor)\n * twice per scene (major)\n * an unlimited number of times per scene (grand)","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"E2XxpwybmLx50WXu","name":"Scimitar dervish","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Extra attack on mastery maneuvers","description":"When attacking with a mastery maneuver while wielding a scimitar, you may make one extra dQck attack against the same or a different target. \nYou may do this\n * once per scene for one point of damage (minor);\n * three times per scene for two points (major);\n * with every mastery attack for two points of damage (grand).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"EYHUBSHqKEevi2JR","name":"Improved critical","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Stronger crits","description":"Your critical hits instead of +2 damage do\n * +3 damage (minor); \n * +4 damage (major); \n * +4 damage and you crit when your opponent rolls a 1, 2, or 3 rather than just a 1 (grand, and note that you still must roll in the top half of your attack range).","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"G0ssrRZkKYtwU4Ek","name":"Martial bloodlines","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Learn additional fighting style","description":"As Fate would have it, you are the scion of a family tree rooted in blood and blossoming with violence. You learn an extra fighting style\n * at the neophyte level (minor);\n * at the apprentice level (major);\n * at the master level (grand);\n\nUnlike other talents, martial bloodlines, once chosen, cannot be \"forgotten\" (not when gaining a level nor any other time).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"HJGkZ6pY4Xewl4BJ","name":"Amulet","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Ignore 2/4/4+ magic damage once per scene","description":"An amulet is the wizard's shield and the witch's refuge. If you have the implement class ability and have selected the amulet, then you ignore \n * the first two points of magic damage you take in a scene (minor)\n * the first four points (major)\n * or the first four points plus one point per magic attack from any creature below level 10 (grand).","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HJGkZ6pY4Xewl4BJ"}}}
{"_id":"HO23CRxjqVFx1GQp","name":"Lace","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Add poison to a spell","description":"Roll your alchemy or poison skill against the Doom. If you succeed, you lace your spell with a poison that you are carrying. If and when your spell does damage, then the poison's effects are added to the spell's effects. If you fail your skill check, the spell has no effect and you must re-cast.\nBonus poison damage:\n * 0 (minor) \n * 1 (major) \n * 2 (grand)\nThe poison is consumed if and only if you succeed in your skill check.","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HO23CRxjqVFx1GQp"}}}
{"_id":"IMyRu1vm4ehx6pmH","name":"Lost","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve organization's ability to hide anything","description":"You add 4 points to your organization's Shadow score when it attempts to hide information, smuggle contraband, sequester a dignitary, or, in general, prevent something from being found. \nWith the major talent, add 6 points.\nWith the grand talent, add 8 points. \n\nIf the bonus points put your Shadow score over 20, you gain a second d20 bonus die instead.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"JbhdvCv4LYP6WPKd","name":"Tactical commander","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve unit's accuracy","description":"When you are in command of a legion in battle, you can use your organization's Force as a bonus die for a non-siege unit's \n * attack roll once per unit (minor);\n * for a unit's attack or defense roll once per unit (major);\n * for a unit's attack and defense roll once per unit, including siege units (grand).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"KFyU8rNlOJyAbDIs","name":"Hold ground","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Resist forced movement","description":"You gain your Strength as a bonus die when resisting attempts to move you in combat.\nYou can use this talent\n * once per scene (minor)\n * three times per scene (major)\n * an unlimited number of times per scene (grand)","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"N0rpksP0jz6T2Vu3","name":"Trap artist","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve your traps","description":"* Increase your relevant die by one size when rolling to see if you successfully set a trap (minor);\n * in addition, the trap does 2 extra points of damage (major);\n * in addition to all of the above, the trap affects two more targets or, if it is already an area of effect trap, it affects a second area (grand).","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"NddfUPTaO71IzVbv","name":"Shutter conscience","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Recover Mood damage","description":"A selective memory is a sinner's friend. You have forgotten more pain, heartbreak, and atrocity than most people have ever seen.\n\nAfter a round finishes, you forget\n * 1 Mood or Inspiration damage you took during that round (minor)\n * 3 Mood or Inspiration damage (major)\n * all Mood and Inspiration damage (grand)\n\nYou cannot use this ability to recoup any Mood you spent yourself or Mood lost to something other than damage. You may do this once per scene; you pick the round immediately after it has finished.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"O1SVigUKNtAu2jOg","name":"Poisoner","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve the potency of poisons you use","description":"Increase the quality level of any poison you use by\n * 1 (minor)\n * 2 (major)\n * 4 (grand)\n\nThis stacks with the Fixer's alchemy ability (and any other relevant ability), but only to a maximum of 6 points higher than listed.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"Ogt6Fthhu3m8tsn7","name":"Steadfast","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Resist Mood damage","description":"When someone tries to damage your Mood during combat, you gain a bonus Heart die to defend, \n * once per scene (minor); \n * three times per scene (major);\n * on every attempt (grand);","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"OpCtZZVGvCA4RE2l","name":"Dugray's feint","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Force Rebalance with  mastery attacks","description":"When executing a mastery maneuver while wielding a one-handed weapon, you can add a dQck feint attack. It does no damage, but if it hits, your opponent is forced to rebalance. You can use this feint\n * once per scene (minor)\n * three times per scene (major)\n * with every mastery attack (grand)","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"QiF58u27oelLp154","name":"Insidious fear","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Instill fear into unlucky people","description":"When a character uses an Inspiration and still fails his roll against you - whether it be in a social attack, chase, combat, or any other scene - you may make an immediate social attack against him.\nIf you win, that character must take one Inspiration point of Fear for you. If he is already at his maximum Inspiration limit, this has no effect. \nYou can use this\n * once per scene (minor)\n * three times per scene (major)\n * an unlimited number of times per scene (grand). As a grand talent, there is no secondary social attack necessary; anyone who fails a roll against you after using an Inspiration instantly gains Fear for you.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"QkJ2vVre1KA3feUM","name":"Staff","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Increase Reason by 1/2/4","description":"The staff is the symbol of wisdom. If you have the implement class ability and have chosen the staff, increase your Reason by \n * 1 (minor)\n * 2 (major)\n * 4 (grand)","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QkJ2vVre1KA3feUM"}}}
{"_id":"Qr7lUSoVByzydkDz","name":"Curse","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Curse a person for day/season/permanently","description":"You can trap your spell not just on an object but on another person. The trap comes with a contingent condition that triggers the spell. The trigger must be an action taken by the victim, not a natural event such as \"every sunrise.\" \"When the victim walks into the sunlight,\" however, does work. The trigger is chosen by you, the caster. The spell functions just as any other trapped spell, except that you must win a Magic vs. Magic roll to set the trap on your target, and nothing will trigger the spell except fulfillment of the trigger condition. You can place a fireball curse that blasts the victim if he sets foot in your city, for example, or a silence spell that activates if the victim starts to say your name. \nThe curse lasts for \n * one day (minor)\n * one season (major)\n * or permanently (grand)\nA grand curse may be triggered more than once, the other curses vanish after one use.","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Qr7lUSoVByzydkDz"}}}
{"_id":"RC0vnLXPCyjmEfy9","name":"The bigger they are","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Extra attack after slaying a big creature","description":"When you slay a creature significantly larger than man-sized, you can cause its hemorrhaging corpse to fall on an enemy. This is\n * a d12 attack for 3 damage against one target (minor);\n * or a d20 attack for 3 damage against up to three targets (major);\n * or a d20 attack for 5 damage + rebalance against up to five targets (grand). \n\nThe targets must be man-sized or smaller.","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"Rymq1GzJvBiv6nww","name":"Sprint and snipe","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Shoot for more damage in chases","description":"In a chase, when you attack with a ranged attack and hit, you deal 1 extra point of damage. \nUse this ability\n * three times per chase (minor);\n * every round (major);\n * every round for 2 extra points (grand);","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"UomBSSGZyjQk3A7k","name":"Field marshal","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Contribute extra command points","description":"When you are in command of a legion in battle, you contribute one extra command point \n * four times per battle (minor); \n * every round (major); \n * every round and you can make reasonable hero actions while still contributing command points (grand).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"ZLUfY6nM01RGxNjd","name":"Sweep the leg","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Add Trip attack on mastery maneuvers","description":"When attacking with a mastery maneuver while wielding a polearm, spiked chain, whip, or similar weapon, or while fighting unarmed, you may add an additional dQck trip attack against your target, forcing him to rebalance if you hit. \nYou may do this\n * once per scene (minor);\n * three times per scene (major);\n * with every mastery attack (grand);","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"bnPrpFh3tlnFB8Aj","name":"Byways","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Your pursuers suffer damage","description":"You can lead a chase through dangerous territory: alleys littered with broken glass, abandoned fixer labs dripping with acid, or the most rat-infested sewer tunnels. When you are in the lead of a chase, you make everyone else roll a supplemental Chase roll against the Doom. Those that fail take 2 points of damage. \nYou can use this ability\n * once per chase (minor);\n * three times per chase (major);\n * three times per chase against a Doom increased by 2 (grand);","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"cb4qJzqfKSUHJqkv","name":"Improved familiar","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Improve familiar's stats","description":"Increase \n * two of your familiar's characteristics by 2 (minor)\n * two of your familiar's characteristics plus his Body by 3 (major)\n * or all of your familiar's characteristics plus his Body by 3 (grand). \n\nAt your GM's option, you may instead (or in addition) add an extension to a special ability, such as adding clairaudience to the raven's clairvoyance, or a second language to the floating skull.","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cb4qJzqfKSUHJqkv"}}}
{"_id":"cmYov3tHDHgodv8L","name":"Brutal slayer","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"One-shot weak enemies with Strength","description":"Pick one type of enemy: undead, giants, descent cats, troglodytes, dragons, etc. Work with your GM to find an appropriate category for the campaign. Humans and trolls are categories that are too broad, but \"Earl Montjaune's Personal Guard\" or \"Templars of the Sun Goddess\" may be appropriate for your campaign.\n\nWhen you hit a target of your chosen type with a mastery maneuver and that foe has three or fewer levels, compare your Strength score to his total Mood + Body (before calculating damage from the blow).\nIf your Strength is equal to or greater than that total, you slay your foe (minor). \n\nUpgrade this to \"six or fewer levels\" at the major level. \n\nUpgrade this to \"nine or fewer levels\" and pick a second type of enemies at the grand level. \n\nYou cannot take this talent twice and thereby gain more slayer target types, nor can you have this talent and Precise Slayer. Too much concentration and single-minded focus is required.","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"e8eohR4djYykS4qv","name":"Hammer knockback","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Push away with mastery attacks","description":"When attacking with a mastery maneuver while wielding a two-handed, blunt weapon such as a maul or great hammer, you may add a dStr attack against your target, pushing your opponent one area away if you hit. \nYou may do this\n * once per scene (minor); \n * three times per scene (major);\n * with every mastery attack (grand);","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"ezBZG9uxoNy6t5XY","name":"Wand","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Use Implement 1/2/5 times more vs. spellbound","description":"A wand is the most popular implement among arcane duelists. If your implement is the wand, you may use your class \"implement\" ability more times per scene as long as the extra uses are against a spellbound creature\n * one extra time (minor)\n * two extra times (major)\n * five extra (grand).","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ezBZG9uxoNy6t5XY"}}}
{"_id":"gg5RoTWKXddGtZiJ","name":"Ley lines","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Gain bonus on magic rolls in a specific location","description":"Pick one location; your magic is concentrated in the land there. Three times per scene, you gain a d10 bonus die on a magic roll you make in that place (including magic attack and defense rolls).\nAt the major level, choose a second location; at the grand level, choose a third location and increase the bonus die to a d12.","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gg5RoTWKXddGtZiJ"}}}
{"_id":"gvH0bwk4dim4nkxh","name":"Master and apprentice","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"They don't interfere and are stronger together","description":"You can be a master and an apprentice. Both casters must have this talent, which functions for both at the master's level (minor, major, or grand). A master must have more magic levels than his apprentice.\n\n * At the minor level, master and apprentice do not count as spellbound for each other, that is, each never causes interference with the other's spells. \n * The major level includes the minor level bonus and also raises the apprentice's Magic score to one below the master's score as long as the pair are in the same area.\n * The grand level includes the major level and also grants each partner a new magic talent as long as both are in the same area.\n\nThe apprentice of your apprentice also counts as your apprentice, and so on, so long master-apprentice chains are possible. Each individual wizard can only have one immediate master and one immediate apprentice. Acquiring a new apprentice or master requires at least one week of attunement and practice.\nA master can dismiss his apprentice's spells or force him to re-cast with a successful Magic vs. Magic roll; this is a free action. \n\nMost masters and apprentices write a covenant with elaborate clauses and subsections detailing their mutual responsibilities and retained rights under scores of different eventualities.","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gvH0bwk4dim4nkxh"}}}
{"_id":"iXoZj5tLWI6EzFyH","name":"Precise slayer","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"One-shot weak enemies with Quickness","description":"Pick one type of enemy: undead, giants, descent cats, troglodytes, dragons, etc. Work with your GM to find an appropriate category for the campaign. Humans and trolls are categories that are too broad, but \"Earl Montjaune's Personal Guard\" or \"Templars of the Sun Goddess\" may be appropriate for your campaign.\n\nWhen you hit a target of your chosen type with a mastery maneuver and that foe has three or fewer levels, compare your Quickness score to his total Mood + Body (before calculating damage from the blow).\nIf your Strength is equal to or greater than that total, you slay your foe (minor). \n\nUpgrade this to \"six or fewer levels\" at the major level. \n\nUpgrade this to \"nine or fewer levels\" and pick a second type of enemies at the grand level. \n\nYou cannot take this talent twice and thereby gain more slayer target types, nor can you have this talent and Precise Slayer. Too much concentration and single-minded focus is required.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"jWEf2amdTAm59vxa","name":"Great weapon overpower","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Debuff enemies with mastery attacks","description":"When attacking with a mastery maneuver while wielding a two-handed weapon, add a dStr attack to your normal attack roll(s). If you hit, your opponent takes a Strength penalty die on all physical rolls next round (physical attacks, defenses, athletic skill or History checks, etc.).\nYou can use this attack\n * once per scene (minor)\n * three times per scene (major)\n * with every mastery attack (grand)","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"jajgR4VJZdI0Ijyc","name":"Death study","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Snatch opponent's item on Disarm","description":"Each round that you remain completely hidden while the target of your study is in combat, you uncover weaknesses in his technique and add +1 damage to your next strike. If you are spotted, your opponent becomes aware of you, you are forced to rebalance, or if you miss with your strike, you lose the bonus damage. \n\nYou can gain a\n * maximum bonus damage of 4 from this maneuver (minor);\n * maximum of 6 but you gain two per round (major);\n * 9 but you gain 3 per round (grand).","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"kMAzUK7vzBL7BiGz","name":"Misdirect","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Feed false impressions to unaware people","description":"When someone fails to see you (that is, you win a hide roll against him), you can misdirect him. \n\nHe thinks\n * you went in a direction of your choice (minor);\n * as previous plus you were carrying, doing, or saying something of your choice (major);\n * as pervious or he sees another person or creature entirely moving in another direction, doing something different, etc. (grand);","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"ldizu7jsAvAKRNUA","name":"Vampiric implement","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Recover damage when casting spells","description":"When you cast a spell with your implement and cause damage to your target, you gain \n * 1 Body or 1 Mood (your choice) (minor); \n * or 1 Body and 1 Mood (major); \n * or 1 Body, 2 Mood, and up to 2 points of characteristic damage you may have suffered (grand)\n\nIn any case, you can never exceed your maximum scores through this vampiric effect, and you can only benefit from this ability once per injury, that is, you cannot use this ability a second time until you have healed to your maximum and are again injured.","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ldizu7jsAvAKRNUA"}}}
{"_id":"n9YfvQ10YUVq4JY2","name":"Magic bloodlines","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Gain beneficial effects","description":"As Fate would have it, magic pulses in your family line like blood in a vein waiting to be tapped. At the minor level, you gain one of the effects listed below (other effects are possible; consult with your group and your GM).\nMinor effects:\n • Glowing eyes (one candlepower each)\n • Touch wilts plants\n • Tattoo birthmark, shifts over weeks\n • Thunderclap when you use an Inspiration\n • Worms surface in your wake when you walk on soil and sometimes other surfaces\n • Your blood is flammable as lantern oil \n\nAt the major level, in addition, you gain a bonus point to Strength, Quickness, Reason, or Charisma that you can assign anew each day.\n\nAt the grand level, in addition to the minor and major effects, you pick one activity: triggering an engineering item, casting a spell, handling animals, leaping, swimming, balancing, etc. You can never change this activity once you pick it. You force the Doom against that activity to increase by 2 for everyone in your area, always, excluding you.\n\nUnlike other talents, magic bloodlines, once chosen, cannot be \"forgotten\" (not when gaining a level nor any other time).","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.n9YfvQ10YUVq4JY2"}}}
{"_id":"nUuaLayDmOwPUrbk","name":"Shield bulwark","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve defense for you and ally","description":"When executing a mastery maneuver and wielding a shield, you gain an additional dStr defense die for you and one ally in your area.\nYou may use this\n * once per scene (minor);\n * three times per scene (major);\n * with every mastery maneuver (grand);","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"ntqTgBgUW2izgd6E","name":"Right people","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"You organization is good at finding info","description":"You know all the right people.\nWhen you or your organization attempts to gain information that can be had by contacting other members of the underworld, lower the Doom\n * by 1 (minor)\n * by 3 (major)\n * by 6 (grand)\n\nDooms of 7 or higher are rare; the grand version of the talent is meant to imply that your friends in the underworld can find out nearly any \"normal secret\" information, leaving only the \"world-changing secret\" information as a challenge.\nYou may use this talent once per topic per week.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"oVcQlUDYM9QraQcz","name":"World is a weapon","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Use environment tricks for free","description":"You are adept at environment tricks. You can add an environment trick to any other chase action at no cost (no modifier to the Doom or the Chase Difficulty, no increased penalty if your trick fails). \nIn combat, you can add an environment trick to any maneuver that includes a move. You can do this\n * once per scene (minor)\n * twice per scene (major)\n * or three times per scene (grand)","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"otBeKcNT62kU6f5Z","name":"Magical beast lord","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Cheaper magical beasts","description":"You and your organization can breed and raise magical beasts at a Wealth Level \n * one below normal (minor)\n * two below normal (major)\n * two below normal with Health and Spirit increased by 2 each (grand)","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.otBeKcNT62kU6f5Z"}}}
{"_id":"pARSfQ9QYS6qHNv4","name":"Parry","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve defense","description":"When wielding a one-handed weapon without a shield, you gain an additional dQck defense die. You can use this ability\n * once per scene (minor)\n * three times per scene (major)\n * three times per scene plus with every mastery maneuver (grand)","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"pRBoxpP8QXpBFV9U","name":"Vizier","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Increase organization's Arcana by 2/4/6","description":"You increase your organization's Arcana score by \n * 2 (minor)\n * 4 (major)\n * 6 (grand)","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pRBoxpP8QXpBFV9U"}}}
{"_id":"rAC3xQ781RrMs9Ly","name":"Fleet commander","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve damage of units","description":"* One zeppelin, naval, or siege unit gains +1 damage on all attacks under your command (minor); \n * up to three such units gain +1 damage on all attacks under your command (major); \n * up to five such units gain +1 damage on all attacks and a free move of 1 area each turn (grand).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"rXvVMahqbStsuXmK","name":"Zur's feedback","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Deal damage back to the caster","description":"When you are hit by a wild surge, you can choose to inflict damage on the caster who caused the surge.\n * 1 point of damage (minor)\n * 2 points of Body damage and 1 point of Magic damage (major) \n * 3 points of Body damage and 3 points of Magic damage (grand)","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"s2QgTkwU6Ibx4DlV","name":"Measure of a man","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Gain info about person's physicality","description":"Roll your martial levels die against the Doom. On a success, you can determine a creature's \n * approximate Body score, Mood score, and martial levels (minor); \n * also his approximate Strength, Quickness, and gear quality (major); \n * also, if you observe him in combat, which fighting styles he knows, which styles he has mastered, and any combat-oriented talents he has (grand).","type":"martial"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"uQrYj4v3oUDsDiCG","name":"Unscathed","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Ignore environment damage in chases","description":"You are accustomed to sliding through curls of riotwire and tumbling off balconies.\nIn a chase, you can ignore damage caused by the environment.\n * 2 points of damage (minor)\n * 4 points of damage (major)\n * 8 points of damage (grand)\n\nYou can split these points up over different rounds.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"vJm0ps7TR2bz2WLu","name":"Combat pick","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Snatch opponent's item on Disarm","description":"When you disarm your opponent in combat, you can make an opposed Quickness check. If you win, you can snatch from your opponent his weapon or one small object worn or carried in sight and accessible (GMs must judge this, as always).\nExamples of such items are dangling earrings, necklaces, fobs, or scabbarded or holstered sidearms such as main-gauches or spare wheellocks.\n\n * With the minor talent, you can take the disarmed man's weapon.\n * With the major talent, you can take the weapon and a small item.\n * With the grand talent, you can take any item the other man is carrying, so long as it is small enough to snatch with one hand.","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"vWcnq7XAciGmmyjo","name":"Shadow general","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Deal bonus damage in shadow wars","description":"When your organization is waging a shadow war, you cause one bonus point of damage when you hit an enemy organization. \nYou can use this ability\n * once every three attacks (minor);\n * once every other attack (major);\n * or every attack (grand);","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"wU7sSBqtHaqTUAYh","name":"Lucre","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Plunder gold in shadow wars","description":"Any time you hit another organization in a shadow war, you gain\n * ten times their scope in gold (minor);\n * twenty times their scope in gold (major);\n * forty times their scope in gold (grand);","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"wnZo4TT0o1Bo67j4","name":"Orb","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Feel magic, read people","description":"Orbs are the symbol of vision and perception.\nIf you have the implement class ability and have chosen the orb, you roll a d20 when attempting to discern if someone is spellbound or not. You can also make a Magic vs. Magic (or Doom, in the case of environments) roll once per target per scene. \n\nWith each roll, you detect any and all of the following: \n * the presence of a spell, invisible or magically hidden objects, undead or other magical creatures (minor); \n * all of the preceding plus the approximate Mood of a man, the approximate characteristics (Str, Qck, etc.) of a man, the fighting and magic styles known by a man, and his surface thoughts over the last minute (major); \n * all of the preceding plus the approximate strengths of a man's Inspirations (though not their source), the Histories of a man and their approximate strengths, and the surface memories of a man going back a number of hours equal to your magic levels (grand).","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wnZo4TT0o1Bo67j4"}}}
{"_id":"xKN8UY40pTczYt7m","name":"Shadow caster","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":1,"short-description":"Become better at concealing magic","description":"You roll your magic levels as a bonus die when attempting to remain hidden while casting a spell or when attempting to avoid being detected as spellbound. \nYou can use this \n * once per scene (minor)\n * three times per scene (major)\n * an unlimited number of times (grand)","type":"magic"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xKN8UY40pTczYt7m"}}}
{"_id":"y4WgpPRKjrDyyaUj","name":"Rend","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Damage stats with mastery attacks","description":"When you hit with a mastery maneuver while wielding a piercing or slashing weapon, you can convert one point of the damage to characteristic damage (Strength, Quickness, or Reason). \nWith the major talent, you can convert up to two points of damage to one point to any two characteristics (out of Strength, Quickness, or Reason, no more than one point per characteristic).\nAs a grand talent, you can convert up to three points of damage to one point to all three characteristics. \n\nYou cannot use rend at the same time that you use another mastery maneuver talent (such as scimitar dervish, hammer knockback, etc.).","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"yVgJoyjFfH3OLUUi","name":"Gambler","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Get good at gambling","description":"Add 4 bonus points to any History that involves gambling. In addition, during a gambling scene, you can re-roll any die or re-draw any card\n * once (minor)\n * three times (major)\n * or every time (grand)","type":"shadow"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"DZgw1W9wWC7Bknih","name":"Administrator","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Increase organization's characteristic","description":"Increase the score of one of your organization's characteristics (Force, Arcana, or Shadow). \n * by 1 (minor)\n * by 3 (major)\n * by 6 (grand)","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"plGpjxGqLtKNuyU5","name":"Audience chamber","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Social attacks have AoE if in specific place","description":"You have an audience chamber, be it a throne room, battlefield command pavilion, or the back room at the Shadows and Sparrows.\nWhen in your audience chamber, your social attacks affect everyone that you are speaking to\n * up to three people (minor)\n * six people (major)\n * everyone in the audience chamber (grand)","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"upsNCsxGfS2D6zRW","name":"Bad","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Gain positive rep from negative rep","description":"You're not just bad for a little while, you're bad for good. \n\n * Pick one negative reputation that you have. You gain a positive reputation at half that value (round up, minimum 4) with a group of your choice. The group must be one that is logically pleased by your negative reputation (usually the enemy of your enemy). \n * With the major talent, pick two negative reputations to gain partnered positive reputations. \n * With the grand talent, pick three. \n\nIf you ever lose the negative reputations, you also lose the associated positive ones.","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"iKGWgCS9zpEZ8ZiA","name":"Bolstering wit","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Restore Mood to allies","description":"Your insults wound their target but amuse everyone else. Once per scene, when you cause Mood damage with a social attack, you also grant 2 Mood points to\n * one ally (minor)\n * three allies (major)\n * all allies (grand).","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"1BtnCcTyrPQwEek3","name":"Contempt","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"More Mood damage against weak people","description":"You have no time to waste on your social inferiors. You deal one additional point of Mood damage with every social attack against any target with less than\n * with less than 3 levels (minor);\n * with 6 or fewer levels (major);\n * with 9 or fewer levels (grand);","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"pdUrcpb7hQGZuP6m","name":"Deflect the blame","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Sacrifice reputation to ignore Mood damage","description":"It's all their fault. You can blame one of your reputation groups instead of yourself, sacrificing an entire positive reputation (it must have at least two points in it) to avoid up to four points of Mood or Reputation damage (from a single attack).\nYou must narrate how you are scapegoating the faction.\n\nAt the major level, you sacrifice 5 reputation points (you need not lose the entire reputation).\n\nAt the grand level, 3 reputation points. \n\nYou can use this ability once per scene.","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"y813umgclHQjgGfP","name":"Emotional paralysis","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Prevent Mood regain","description":"After you win a social scene, your opponent (pick one if there are many) cannot gain Mood for\n * one day (minor);\n * two days (major);\n * a week (grand). The grand talent also prevents the opponent from gaining Inspiration points.","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"kBVsbeKuupBvSTxx","name":"Fashion kills","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve your fashion","description":"Treat any fashion item that you use in a social scene as\n * one Quality point higher than it really is (minor);\n * two points higher (major);\n * four points higher (grand);","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"CdNxOneh3e3tipJg","name":"Fashion maven","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Use more fashion items","description":"You can use\n * a second fashion item for a social attack or defense die in a scene (minor);\n * a second and a third item (major);\n * three items including the same one twice (grand);","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"pWRQH4xXNGqGaEhW","name":"Inspirational leader","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve unit's accuracy","description":"A unit in your army can roll your Charisma as a bonus die on any roll. You can use this ability\n * once per battle (minor)\n * twice per battle (major)\n * four times per battle (grand)","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"RdAPnfo5fDIbJXZO","name":"Keen eye","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Study person to get info/leverage","description":"Roll your social levels die or your Reason against the Doom. On a success, you can ascertain a character's Mood, Wealth Level, and home region simply by studying him as he interacts with others for a few minutes.\n\nWith the major talent, you learn all of the above, plus all class titles he has earned and the general areas of his Inspirations (but not their specific sources). \n\nWith the grand talent, you learn all of the above, and you can adapt your approach so that, when interacting with the target of your study, your Charisma is two points higher than normal. \n\n(NB: The preceding assumes the target of your study is not trying to actively conceal his nature. If he is, then rather than roll against the Doom, make an opposed Charisma check.)","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"lJLhFAXQa1dg8j3n","name":"Manager","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Increase organization's Efficiency","description":"Increase the Efficiency of your Organization by\n * 1 (minor)\n * 3 (major)\n * 5 and increase another characteristic by 2 (grand)","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"udsPkC56E12fX1Ah","name":"Moral support","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Improve ally's social defense","description":"You can allow an ally to roll your Charisma as a bonus social defense die. \nYou can do this\n * once per scene (minor)\n * twice per scene (major)\n * or four times per scene (grand)","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"ltpnPrEXkhL6b6sH","name":"Moved by propinquity","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Use person focused inspirations more","description":"If the focus of your Inspiration is another person and she is present in your area, you may use that Inspiration one extra time per scene. \n\nWith the major talent, you can do the same but your Inspiration need only be less than a handful of areas away.\n\nWith the grand talent, you can use this ability as long as you saw your Inspiration sometime today.","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"FEnvOkRwyXdEPFaT","name":"Nemesis","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Get better against a person in social combat","description":"Pick one of your social tormentors.\nWhen resisting her or attacking her in a social scene, treat your Charisma as if it were\n * 2 points higher (minor);\n * 4 points higher (major);\n * 6 points higher (grand);","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"w5vaZMqjXJZmNE0h","name":"Public relations","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Gain benefits for being popular","description":"You are a master at public relations.\nFor every positive reputation you have at 7 or higher, you gain a gift from the admiring multitudes.\n\nIf your reputation is 7 or higher, you gain one item of Wealth Level 9 or less (minor). Impoverished populations may present you with land, livestock, slaves, advantageous marriages, or lionizing skalds instead of an item listed in the Equipment chapter.\n\nIn addition, if your reputation is 11-15 and you have the major version of this talent, you gain a statue and a holiday.\nThe statue grants you a new reputation, Memorialized (6), with anyone who sees the statue. In a region that celebrates your holiday, on that day, your maximum Mood increases to 6 above its maximum, and you receive as tribute one item of Wealth Level equal to your character level.\n\nFinally, if your reputation is 16 or more and you have the grand version of this talent, your public clamors for you to be granted a noble title or for you to be beatified. As a living saint, you roll a d20 bonus die in each and every dealing with the Church, you may claim canon law regardless of location, and you command the respect and awe of a saint (which the GM must judge).","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"1givkPUOKaIdNDhD","name":"Reasoned defense","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Defend with Reason in social combat","description":"You can defend against a social attack using your Reason rather than your Charisma.\nYou can do this\n * once per encounter (minor);\n * three times per encounter (major);\n * every time (grand);","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"ZbdfePiU1XB94zSm","name":"Ridicule","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"More damage in social combat","description":"When you make a social attack against anyone whose highest Wealth Level fashion item is 4 or more levels below your highest Wealth Level fashion item, you do one additional point of damage.\nYou can do this\n * once per scene (minor);\n * three times (major);\n * with every attack (grand);","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"k1eksGNaD4CMlvHd","name":"Rumors","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Change person's reputation","description":"Once per week, you can launch a rumor with sufficient traction that it damages or bolsters someone's reputation. Roll your Charisma against the Doom (to help) or your opponent's Charisma (to harm). If you succeed, you alter one of your target's reputations by one, up or down according to the rumor you spread. This is a minor talent. \n\nThe major talent allows you to hit two different targets in a week. \n\nThe grand allows you to hit three different targets per week.","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"UDpMon60TOD8yYwF","name":"Secret sharer","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Increase ally's max Mood","description":"You tempt people into divulging their secrets. When a person confides a secret in you, she increases her maximum Mood by 1. This lasts until the secret is no longer a secret (whether you sold it or whether it was exposed through another eventuality).\n\nAt the minor level, you can share one secret each from three people.\n\nAt the major level, you can share two secrets each from four people.\n\nAt the grand level, you can share two secrets each from a number of people equal to your Charisma.","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"838CU6vjihX60Ahy","name":"Spiritual leader","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Restore more Spirit when unit is rallied","description":"Your organization restores 2 Spirit points rather than 1 when it rallies a troop or unit in a battle. \nYou can use this ability\n * once per unit (minor);\n * twice per unit for 3 Spirit points (major);\n * an unlimited number of times for 3 Spirit points (grand);","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
{"_id":"tVO8wz2EwPsCSWrw","name":"Stake your word on it","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"level":"1","short-description":"Bet reputation to do more Mood damage","description":"Choose a reputation of yours that covers your target and attack him with a social attack. If you hit, you do one extra point of damage, but if you miss, you lose one reputation point. \n\nPer attack, you can risk up to\n * 1 reputation point (minor)\n * 2 reputation points (major)\n * 4 reputation points (grand) \n\nEach risked reputation point causes 1 extra point of damage; if you miss, all risked reputation points are lost. \n\nYou can use this talent once per scene per target.","type":"social"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"99ZnDWtH2QTzrxxi":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rXvVMahqbStsuXmK"}}}
